         <abstract>
            <p>This paper discusses developing renewable power projects in a multi-country Joint Venture (JV) environment. A number of key factors in doing JV renewable power projects are analysed which cover Power Purchase Agreements (PPA), JV arrangements, project company structures and financing structures. A commonly preferred procedure for JV power project development is set out. First hand experiences are also reported to illustrate potential loopholes in JV renewable power project management.</p>
         </abstract>
